Implement the requested Python function in solution.py. Run the tests.

Write a function to count the element frequency in the mixed nested tuple.

Your code must pass these tests:
assert count_element_freq((5, 6, (5, 6), 7, (8, 9), 9) ) == {5: 2, 6: 2, 7: 1, 8: 1, 9: 2}
assert count_element_freq((6, 7, (6, 7), 8, (9, 10), 10) ) == {6: 2, 7: 2, 8: 1, 9: 1, 10: 2}
assert count_element_freq((7, 8, (7, 8), 9, (10, 11), 11) ) == {7: 2, 8: 2, 9: 1, 10: 1, 11: 2}

The project is at data/blueprints/mbpp_512.

Implement the requested Python function in solution.py. Run the tests.

Write a function to assign with each element, its pair elements from other similar pairs in the given tuple.

Your code must pass these tests:
assert assign_elements([(5, 3), (7, 5), (2, 7), (3, 8), (8, 4)] ) == {3: [8], 5: [3], 7: [5], 2: [7], 8: [4], 4: []}
assert assign_elements([(6, 4), (9, 4), (3, 8), (4, 9), (9, 5)] ) == {4: [9], 6: [4], 9: [4, 5], 8: [], 3: [8], 5: []}
assert assign_elements([(6, 2), (6, 8), (4, 9), (4, 9), (3, 7)] ) == {2: [], 6: [2, 8], 8: [], 9: [], 4: [9, 9], 7: [], 3: [7]}

The project is at data/blueprints/mbpp_561.
